31struct vp8_extracfg {
32 struct vpx_codec_pkt_list *pkt_list;
33 int cpu_used; /** available cpu percentage in 1/16*/
34 /** if encoder decides to uses alternate reference frame */
35 unsigned int enable_auto_alt_ref;
36 unsigned int noise_sensitivity;
37 unsigned int Sharpness;
38 unsigned int static_thresh;
39 unsigned int token_partitions;
40 unsigned int arnr_max_frames; /* alt_ref Noise Reduction Max Frame Count */
41 unsigned int arnr_strength; /* alt_ref Noise Reduction Strength */
42 unsigned int arnr_type; /* alt_ref filter type */
43 vp8e_tuning tuning;
44 unsigned int cq_level; /* constrained quality level */
45 unsigned int rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct;
46 unsigned int gf_cbr_boost_pct;
47 unsigned int screen_content_mode;
48};
49
50static struct vp8_extracfg default_extracfg = {
51 NULL,
52#if !(CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY)
53 0, /* cpu_used */
54#else
55 4, /* cpu_used */
56#endif
57 0, /* enable_auto_alt_ref */
58 0, /* noise_sensitivity */
59 0, /* Sharpness */
60 0, /* static_thresh */
61#if (CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY & CONFIG_ONTHEFLY_BITPACKING)
62 VP8_EIGHT_TOKENPARTITION,
63#else
64 VP8_ONE_TOKENPARTITION, /* token_partitions */
65#endif
66 0, /* arnr_max_frames */
67 3, /* arnr_strength */
68 3, /* arnr_type*/
69 0, /* tuning*/
70 10, /* cq_level */
71 0, /* rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct */
72 0, /* gf_cbr_boost_pct */
73 0, /* screen_content_mode */
74};

76struct vpx_codec_alg_priv {
77 vpx_codec_priv_t base;
78 vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t cfg;
79 struct vp8_extracfg vp8_cfg;
80 vpx_rational64_t timestamp_ratio;
81 vpx_codec_pts_t pts_offset;
82 unsigned char pts_offset_initialized;
83 VP8_CONFIG oxcf;
84 struct VP8_COMP *cpi;
85 unsigned char *cx_data;
86 unsigned int cx_data_sz;
87 vpx_image_t preview_img;
88 unsigned int next_frame_flag;
89 vp8_postproc_cfg_t preview_ppcfg;
90 /* pkt_list size depends on the maximum number of lagged frames allowed. */
91 vpx_codec_pkt_list_decl(64) pkt_list;
92 unsigned int fixed_kf_cntr;
93 vpx_enc_frame_flags_t control_frame_flags;
94};

96static vpx_codec_err_t update_error_state(
97 vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, const struct vpx_internal_error_info *error) {
98 vpx_codec_err_t res;
99
100 if ((res = error->error_code)) {
101 ctx->base.err_detail = error->has_detail ? error->detail : NULL;
102 }
103
104 return res;
105}
106
107#undef ERROR
108#define ERROR(str) \
109 do { \
110 ctx->base.err_detail = str; \
111 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM; \
112 } while (0)
113
114#define RANGE_CHECK(p, memb, lo, hi) \
115 do { \
116 if (!(((p)->memb == (lo) || (p)->memb > (lo)) && (p)->memb <= (hi))) \
117 ERROR(#memb " out of range [" #lo ".." #hi "]"); \
118 } while (0)
119
120#define RANGE_CHECK_HI(p, memb, hi) \
121 do { \
122 if (!((p)->memb <= (hi))) ERROR(#memb " out of range [.." #hi "]"); \
123 } while (0)
124
125#define RANGE_CHECK_LO(p, memb, lo) \
126 do { \
127 if (!((p)->memb >= (lo))) ERROR(#memb " out of range [" #lo "..]"); \
128 } while (0)
129
130#define RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(p, memb) \
131 do { \
132 if (!!((p)->memb) != (p)->memb) ERROR(#memb " expected boolean"); \
133 } while (0)
134
135static vpx_codec_err_t validate_config(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
136 const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg,
137 const struct vp8_extracfg *vp8_cfg,
138 int finalize) {
139 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_w, 1, 16383); /* 14 bits available */
140 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_h, 1, 16383); /* 14 bits available */
141 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_timebase.den, 1, 1000000000);
142 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_timebase.num, 1, 1000000000);
143 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_profile, 3);
144 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_max_quantizer, 63);
145 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_min_quantizer, cfg->rc_max_quantizer);
146 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_threads, 64);
147#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
148 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_lag_in_frames, 0);
149#elif CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
150 if (ctx->base.enc.total_encoders > 1) RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_lag_in_frames, 0);
151#else
152 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_lag_in_frames, 25);
153#endif
154 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, rc_end_usage, VPX_VBR, VPX_Q);
155 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_undershoot_pct, 1000);
156 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_overshoot_pct, 1000);
157 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_2pass_vbr_bias_pct, 100);
158 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, kf_mode, VPX_KF_DISABLED, VPX_KF_AUTO);
159
160/* TODO: add spatial re-sampling support and frame dropping in
161 * multi-res-encoder.*/
162#if CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
163 if (ctx->base.enc.total_encoders > 1)
164 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_resize_allowed, 0);
165#else
166 RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(cfg, rc_resize_allowed);
167#endif
168 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_dropframe_thresh, 100);
169 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_resize_up_thresh, 100);
170 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_resize_down_thresh, 100);
171
172#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
173 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_pass, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS);
174#elif CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
175 if (ctx->base.enc.total_encoders > 1)
176 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_pass, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS);
177#else
178 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_pass, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS, VPX_RC_LAST_PASS);
179#endif
180
181 /* VP8 does not support a lower bound on the keyframe interval in
182 * automatic keyframe placement mode.
183 */
184 if (cfg->kf_mode != VPX_KF_DISABLED && cfg->kf_min_dist != cfg->kf_max_dist &&
185 cfg->kf_min_dist > 0)
186 ERROR(
187 "kf_min_dist not supported in auto mode, use 0 "
188 "or kf_max_dist instead.");
189
190 RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(vp8_cfg, enable_auto_alt_ref);
191 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, cpu_used, -16, 16);
192
193#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY && !CONFIG_TEMPORAL_DENOISING
194 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, noise_sensitivity, 0, 0);
195#else
196 RANGE_CHECK_HI(vp8_cfg, noise_sensitivity, 6);
197#endif
198
199 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, token_partitions, VP8_ONE_TOKENPARTITION,
200 VP8_EIGHT_TOKENPARTITION);
201 RANGE_CHECK_HI(vp8_cfg, Sharpness, 7);
202 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, arnr_max_frames, 0, 15);
203 RANGE_CHECK_HI(vp8_cfg, arnr_strength, 6);
204 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, arnr_type, 1, 3);
205 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, cq_level, 0, 63);
206 RANGE_CHECK_HI(vp8_cfg, screen_content_mode, 2);
207 if (finalize && (cfg->rc_end_usage == VPX_CQ || cfg->rc_end_usage == VPX_Q))
208 RANGE_CHECK(vp8_cfg, cq_level, cfg->rc_min_quantizer,
209 cfg->rc_max_quantizer);
210
211#if !(CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY)
212 if (cfg->g_pass == VPX_RC_LAST_PASS) {
213 size_t packet_sz = sizeof(FIRSTPASS_STATS);
214 int n_packets = (int)(cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz / packet_sz);
215 FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats;
216
217 if (!cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf)
218 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in.buf not set.");
219
220 if (cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz % packet_sz)
221 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in.sz indicates truncated packet.");
222
223 if (cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz < 2 * packet_sz)
224 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in requires at least two packets.");
225
226 stats = (void *)((char *)cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf +
227 (n_packets - 1) * packet_sz);
228
229 if ((int)(stats->count + 0.5) != n_packets - 1)
230 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in missing EOS stats packet");
231 }
232#endif
233
234 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, ts_number_layers, 1, 5);
235
236 if (cfg->ts_number_layers > 1) {
237 unsigned int i;
238 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, ts_periodicity, 16);
239
240 for (i = 1; i < cfg->ts_number_layers; ++i) {
241 if (cfg->ts_target_bitrate[i] <= cfg->ts_target_bitrate[i - 1] &&
242 cfg->rc_target_bitrate > 0)
243 ERROR("ts_target_bitrate entries are not strictly increasing");
244 }
245
246 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, ts_rate_decimator[cfg->ts_number_layers - 1], 1, 1);
247 for (i = cfg->ts_number_layers - 2; i > 0; i--) {
248 if (cfg->ts_rate_decimator[i - 1] != 2 * cfg->ts_rate_decimator[i])
249 ERROR("ts_rate_decimator factors are not powers of 2");
250 }
251
252 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, ts_layer_id[i], cfg->ts_number_layers - 1);
253 }
254
255#if (CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY & CONFIG_ONTHEFLY_BITPACKING)
256 if (cfg->g_threads > (1 << vp8_cfg->token_partitions))
257 ERROR("g_threads cannot be bigger than number of token partitions");
258#endif
259
260 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
261}
262
263static vpx_codec_err_t validate_img(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
264 const vpx_image_t *img) {
265 switch (img->fmt) {
266 case VPX_IMG_FMT_YV12:
267 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I420:
268 case VPX_IMG_FMT_NV12: break;
269 default:
270 ERROR(
271 "Invalid image format. Only YV12, I420 and NV12 images are "
272 "supported");
273 }
274
275 if ((img->d_w != ctx->cfg.g_w) || (img->d_h != ctx->cfg.g_h))
276 ERROR("Image size must match encoder init configuration size");
277
278 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
279}

281static vpx_codec_err_t set_vp8e_config(VP8_CONFIG *oxcf,
282 vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t cfg,
283 struct vp8_extracfg vp8_cfg,
284 vpx_codec_priv_enc_mr_cfg_t *mr_cfg) {
285 oxcf->multi_threaded = cfg.g_threads;
286 oxcf->Version = cfg.g_profile;
287
288 oxcf->Width = cfg.g_w;
289 oxcf->Height = cfg.g_h;
290 oxcf->timebase = cfg.g_timebase;
291
292 oxcf->error_resilient_mode = cfg.g_error_resilient;
293
294 switch (cfg.g_pass) {
295 case VPX_RC_ONE_PASS: oxcf->Mode = MODE_BESTQUALITY; break;
296 case VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS: oxcf->Mode = MODE_FIRSTPASS; break;
297 case VPX_RC_LAST_PASS: oxcf->Mode = MODE_SECONDPASS_BEST; break;
298 }
299
300 if (cfg.g_pass == VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS || cfg.g_pass == VPX_RC_ONE_PASS) {
301 oxcf->allow_lag = 0;
302 oxcf->lag_in_frames = 0;
303 } else {
304 oxcf->allow_lag = (cfg.g_lag_in_frames) > 0;
305 oxcf->lag_in_frames = cfg.g_lag_in_frames;
306 }
307
308 oxcf->allow_df = (cfg.rc_dropframe_thresh > 0);
309 oxcf->drop_frames_water_mark = cfg.rc_dropframe_thresh;
310
311 oxcf->allow_spatial_resampling = cfg.rc_resize_allowed;
312 oxcf->resample_up_water_mark = cfg.rc_resize_up_thresh;
313 oxcf->resample_down_water_mark = cfg.rc_resize_down_thresh;
314
315 if (cfg.rc_end_usage == VPX_VBR) {
316 oxcf->end_usage = USAGE_LOCAL_FILE_PLAYBACK;
317 } else if (cfg.rc_end_usage == VPX_CBR) {
318 oxcf->end_usage = USAGE_STREAM_FROM_SERVER;
319 } else if (cfg.rc_end_usage == VPX_CQ) {
320 oxcf->end_usage = USAGE_CONSTRAINED_QUALITY;
321 } else if (cfg.rc_end_usage == VPX_Q) {
322 oxcf->end_usage = USAGE_CONSTANT_QUALITY;
323 }
324
325 oxcf->target_bandwidth = cfg.rc_target_bitrate;
326 oxcf->rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct = vp8_cfg.rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct;
327 oxcf->gf_cbr_boost_pct = vp8_cfg.gf_cbr_boost_pct;
328
329 oxcf->best_allowed_q = cfg.rc_min_quantizer;
330 oxcf->worst_allowed_q = cfg.rc_max_quantizer;
331 oxcf->cq_level = vp8_cfg.cq_level;
332 oxcf->fixed_q = -1;
333
334 oxcf->under_shoot_pct = cfg.rc_undershoot_pct;
335 oxcf->over_shoot_pct = cfg.rc_overshoot_pct;
336
337 oxcf->maximum_buffer_size_in_ms = cfg.rc_buf_sz;
338 oxcf->starting_buffer_level_in_ms = cfg.rc_buf_initial_sz;
339 oxcf->optimal_buffer_level_in_ms = cfg.rc_buf_optimal_sz;
340
341 oxcf->maximum_buffer_size = cfg.rc_buf_sz;
342 oxcf->starting_buffer_level = cfg.rc_buf_initial_sz;
343 oxcf->optimal_buffer_level = cfg.rc_buf_optimal_sz;
344
345 oxcf->two_pass_vbrbias = cfg.rc_2pass_vbr_bias_pct;
346 oxcf->two_pass_vbrmin_section = cfg.rc_2pass_vbr_minsection_pct;
347 oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section = cfg.rc_2pass_vbr_maxsection_pct;
348
349 oxcf->auto_key =
350 cfg.kf_mode == VPX_KF_AUTO && cfg.kf_min_dist != cfg.kf_max_dist;
351 oxcf->key_freq = cfg.kf_max_dist;
352
353 oxcf->number_of_layers = cfg.ts_number_layers;
354 oxcf->periodicity = cfg.ts_periodicity;
355
356 if (oxcf->number_of_layers > 1) {
357 memcpy(oxcf->target_bitrate, cfg.ts_target_bitrate,
358 sizeof(cfg.ts_target_bitrate));
359 memcpy(oxcf->rate_decimator, cfg.ts_rate_decimator,
360 sizeof(cfg.ts_rate_decimator));
361 memcpy(oxcf->layer_id, cfg.ts_layer_id, sizeof(cfg.ts_layer_id));
362 }
363
364#if CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
365 /* When mr_cfg is NULL, oxcf->mr_total_resolutions and oxcf->mr_encoder_id
366 * are both memset to 0, which ensures the correct logic under this
367 * situation.
368 */
369 if (mr_cfg) {
370 oxcf->mr_total_resolutions = mr_cfg->mr_total_resolutions;
371 oxcf->mr_encoder_id = mr_cfg->mr_encoder_id;
372 oxcf->mr_down_sampling_factor.num = mr_cfg->mr_down_sampling_factor.num;
373 oxcf->mr_down_sampling_factor.den = mr_cfg->mr_down_sampling_factor.den;
374 oxcf->mr_low_res_mode_info = mr_cfg->mr_low_res_mode_info;
375 }
376#else
377 (void)mr_cfg;
378#endif
379
380 oxcf->cpu_used = vp8_cfg.cpu_used;
381 oxcf->encode_breakout = vp8_cfg.static_thresh;
382 oxcf->play_alternate = vp8_cfg.enable_auto_alt_ref;
383 oxcf->noise_sensitivity = vp8_cfg.noise_sensitivity;
384 oxcf->Sharpness = vp8_cfg.Sharpness;
385 oxcf->token_partitions = vp8_cfg.token_partitions;
386
387 oxcf->two_pass_stats_in = cfg.rc_twopass_stats_in;
388 oxcf->output_pkt_list = vp8_cfg.pkt_list;
389
390 oxcf->arnr_max_frames = vp8_cfg.arnr_max_frames;
391 oxcf->arnr_strength = vp8_cfg.arnr_strength;
392 oxcf->arnr_type = vp8_cfg.arnr_type;
393
394 oxcf->tuning = vp8_cfg.tuning;
395
396 oxcf->screen_content_mode = vp8_cfg.screen_content_mode;
397
398 /*
399 printf("Current VP8 Settings: \n");
400 printf("target_bandwidth: %d\n", oxcf->target_bandwidth);
401 printf("noise_sensitivity: %d\n", oxcf->noise_sensitivity);
402 printf("Sharpness: %d\n", oxcf->Sharpness);
403 printf("cpu_used: %d\n", oxcf->cpu_used);
404 printf("Mode: %d\n", oxcf->Mode);
405 printf("auto_key: %d\n", oxcf->auto_key);
406 printf("key_freq: %d\n", oxcf->key_freq);
407 printf("end_usage: %d\n", oxcf->end_usage);
408 printf("under_shoot_pct: %d\n", oxcf->under_shoot_pct);
409 printf("over_shoot_pct: %d\n", oxcf->over_shoot_pct);
410 printf("starting_buffer_level: %d\n", oxcf->starting_buffer_level);
411 printf("optimal_buffer_level: %d\n", oxcf->optimal_buffer_level);
412 printf("maximum_buffer_size: %d\n", oxcf->maximum_buffer_size);
413 printf("fixed_q: %d\n", oxcf->fixed_q);
414 printf("worst_allowed_q: %d\n", oxcf->worst_allowed_q);
415 printf("best_allowed_q: %d\n", oxcf->best_allowed_q);
416 printf("allow_spatial_resampling: %d\n", oxcf->allow_spatial_resampling);
417 printf("resample_down_water_mark: %d\n", oxcf->resample_down_water_mark);
418 printf("resample_up_water_mark: %d\n", oxcf->resample_up_water_mark);
419 printf("allow_df: %d\n", oxcf->allow_df);
420 printf("drop_frames_water_mark: %d\n", oxcf->drop_frames_water_mark);
421 printf("two_pass_vbrbias: %d\n", oxcf->two_pass_vbrbias);
422 printf("two_pass_vbrmin_section: %d\n", oxcf->two_pass_vbrmin_section);
423 printf("two_pass_vbrmax_section: %d\n", oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section);
424 printf("allow_lag: %d\n", oxcf->allow_lag);
425 printf("lag_in_frames: %d\n", oxcf->lag_in_frames);
426 printf("play_alternate: %d\n", oxcf->play_alternate);
427 printf("Version: %d\n", oxcf->Version);
428 printf("multi_threaded: %d\n", oxcf->multi_threaded);
429 printf("encode_breakout: %d\n", oxcf->encode_breakout);
430 */
431 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
432}

434static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_set_config(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
435 const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg) {
436 vpx_codec_err_t res;
437
438 if (cfg->g_w != ctx->cfg.g_w || cfg->g_h != ctx->cfg.g_h) {
439 if (cfg->g_lag_in_frames > 1 || cfg->g_pass != VPX_RC_ONE_PASS)
440 ERROR("Cannot change width or height after initialization");
441 if ((ctx->cpi->initial_width && (int)cfg->g_w > ctx->cpi->initial_width) ||
442 (ctx->cpi->initial_height && (int)cfg->g_h > ctx->cpi->initial_height))
443 ERROR("Cannot increase width or height larger than their initial values");
444 }
445
446 /* Prevent increasing lag_in_frames. This check is stricter than it needs
447 * to be -- the limit is not increasing past the first lag_in_frames
448 * value, but we don't track the initial config, only the last successful
449 * config.
450 */
451 if ((cfg->g_lag_in_frames > ctx->cfg.g_lag_in_frames))
452 ERROR("Cannot increase lag_in_frames");
453
454 res = validate_config(ctx, cfg, &ctx->vp8_cfg, 0);
455
456 if (!res) {
457 ctx->cfg = *cfg;
458 set_vp8e_config(&ctx->oxcf, ctx->cfg, ctx->vp8_cfg, NULL);
459 vp8_change_config(ctx->cpi, &ctx->oxcf);
460 }
461
462 return res;
463}
464
465static vpx_codec_err_t get_quantizer(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, va_list args) {
466 int *const arg = va_arg(args, int *);
467 if (arg == NULL) return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
468 *arg = vp8_get_quantizer(ctx->cpi);
469 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
470}
471
472static vpx_codec_err_t get_quantizer64(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
473 va_list args) {
474 int *const arg = va_arg(args, int *);
475 if (arg == NULL) return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
476 *arg = vp8_reverse_trans(vp8_get_quantizer(ctx->cpi));
477 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
478}
479
480static vpx_codec_err_t update_extracfg(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
481 const struct vp8_extracfg *extra_cfg) {
482 const vpx_codec_err_t res = validate_config(ctx, &ctx->cfg, extra_cfg, 0);
483 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) {
484 ctx->vp8_cfg = *extra_cfg;
485 set_vp8e_config(&ctx->oxcf, ctx->cfg, ctx->vp8_cfg, NULL);
486 vp8_change_config(ctx->cpi, &ctx->oxcf);
487 }
488 return res;
489}
490
491static vpx_codec_err_t set_cpu_used(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, va_list args) {
492 struct vp8_extracfg extra_cfg = ctx->vp8_cfg;
493 extra_cfg.cpu_used = CAST(VP8E_SET_CPUUSED, args);
494 // Use fastest speed setting (speed 16 or -16) if it's set beyond the range.
495 extra_cfg.cpu_used = VPXMIN(16, extra_cfg.cpu_used);
496 extra_cfg.cpu_used = VPXMAX(-16, extra_cfg.cpu_used);
497 return update_extracfg(ctx, &extra_cfg);
498}
499
500static vpx_codec_err_t set_enable_auto_alt_ref(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
501 va_list args) {
502 struct vp8_extracfg extra_cfg = ctx->vp8_cfg;
503 extra_cfg.enable_auto_alt_ref = CAST(VP8E_SET_ENABLEAUTOALTREF, args);
504 return update_extracfg(ctx, &extra_cfg);
505}
506
507static vpx_codec_err_t set_noise_sensitivity(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
508 va_list args) {
509 struct vp8_extracfg extra_cfg = ctx->vp8_cfg;
510 extra_cfg.noise_sensitivity = CAST(VP8E_SET_NOISE_SENSITIVITY, args);
511 return update_extracfg(ctx, &extra_cfg);
512}

514static vpx_codec_err_t set_sharpness(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, va_list args) {
515 struct vp8_extracfg extra_cfg = ctx->vp8_cfg;
516 extra_cfg.Sharpness = CAST(VP8E_SET_SHARPNESS, args);

588static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_mr_alloc_mem(const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg,
589 void **mem_loc) {
590 vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
591
592#if CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
593 LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO *shared_mem_loc;
594 int mb_rows = ((cfg->g_w + 15) >> 4);
595 int mb_cols = ((cfg->g_h + 15) >> 4);
596
597 shared_mem_loc = calloc(1, sizeof(LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO));
598 if (!shared_mem_loc) {
599 return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
600 }
601
602 shared_mem_loc->mb_info =
603 calloc(mb_rows * mb_cols, sizeof(LOWER_RES_MB_INFO));
604 if (!(shared_mem_loc->mb_info)) {
605 free(shared_mem_loc);
606 res = VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
607 } else {
608 *mem_loc = (void *)shared_mem_loc;
609 res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
610 }
611#else
612 (void)cfg;
613 (void)mem_loc;
614#endif
615 return res;
616}
617
618static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_init(vpx_codec_ctx_t *ctx,
619 vpx_codec_priv_enc_mr_cfg_t *mr_cfg) {
620 vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
621
622 vp8_rtcd();
623 vpx_dsp_rtcd();
624 vpx_scale_rtcd();
625
626 if (!ctx->priv) {
627 struct vpx_codec_alg_priv *priv =
628 (struct vpx_codec_alg_priv *)vpx_calloc(1, sizeof(*priv));
629
630 if (!priv) {
631 return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
632 }
633
634 ctx->priv = (vpx_codec_priv_t *)priv;
635 ctx->priv->init_flags = ctx->init_flags;
636
637 if (ctx->config.enc) {
638 /* Update the reference to the config structure to an
639 * internal copy.
640 */
641 priv->cfg = *ctx->config.enc;
642 ctx->config.enc = &priv->cfg;
643 }
644
645 priv->vp8_cfg = default_extracfg;
646 priv->vp8_cfg.pkt_list = &priv->pkt_list.head;
647
648 priv->cx_data_sz = priv->cfg.g_w * priv->cfg.g_h * 3 / 2 * 2;
649
650 if (priv->cx_data_sz < 32768) priv->cx_data_sz = 32768;
651
652 priv->cx_data = malloc(priv->cx_data_sz);
653
654 if (!priv->cx_data) {
655 return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
656 }
657
658 if (mr_cfg) {
659 ctx->priv->enc.total_encoders = mr_cfg->mr_total_resolutions;
660 } else {
661 ctx->priv->enc.total_encoders = 1;
662 }
663
664 once(vp8_initialize_enc);
665
666 res = validate_config(priv, &priv->cfg, &priv->vp8_cfg, 0);
667
668 if (!res) {
669 priv->pts_offset_initialized = 0;
670 priv->timestamp_ratio.den = priv->cfg.g_timebase.den;
671 priv->timestamp_ratio.num = (int64_t)priv->cfg.g_timebase.num;
672 priv->timestamp_ratio.num *= TICKS_PER_SEC;
673 reduce_ratio(&priv->timestamp_ratio);
674
675 set_vp8e_config(&priv->oxcf, priv->cfg, priv->vp8_cfg, mr_cfg);
676 priv->cpi = vp8_create_compressor(&priv->oxcf);
677 if (!priv->cpi) res = VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
678 }
679 }
680
681 return res;
682}
683
684static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_destroy(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx) {
685#if CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
686 /* Free multi-encoder shared memory */
687 if (ctx->oxcf.mr_total_resolutions > 0 &&
688 (ctx->oxcf.mr_encoder_id == ctx->oxcf.mr_total_resolutions - 1)) {
689 LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO *shared_mem_loc =
690 (LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO *)ctx->oxcf.mr_low_res_mode_info;
691 free(shared_mem_loc->mb_info);
692 free(ctx->oxcf.mr_low_res_mode_info);
693 }
694#endif
695
696 free(ctx->cx_data);
697 vp8_remove_compressor(&ctx->cpi);
698 vpx_free(ctx);
699 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
700}
701
702static vpx_codec_err_t image2yuvconfig(const vpx_image_t *img,
703 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *yv12) {
704 const int y_w = img->d_w;
705 const int y_h = img->d_h;
706 const int uv_w = (img->d_w + 1) / 2;
707 const int uv_h = (img->d_h + 1) / 2;
708 vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
709 yv12->y_buffer = img->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y];
710 yv12->u_buffer = img->planes[VPX_PLANE_U];
711 yv12->v_buffer = img->planes[VPX_PLANE_V];
712
713 yv12->y_crop_width = y_w;
714 yv12->y_crop_height = y_h;
715 yv12->y_width = y_w;
716 yv12->y_height = y_h;
717 yv12->uv_crop_width = uv_w;
718 yv12->uv_crop_height = uv_h;
719 yv12->uv_width = uv_w;
720 yv12->uv_height = uv_h;
721
722 yv12->y_stride = img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y];
723 yv12->uv_stride = img->stride[VPX_PLANE_U];
724
725 yv12->border = (img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] - img->w) / 2;
726 return res;
727}
728
729static void pick_quickcompress_mode(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
730 unsigned long duration,
731 unsigned long deadline) {
732 int new_qc;
733
734#if !(CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY)
735 /* Use best quality mode if no deadline is given. */
736 new_qc = MODE_BESTQUALITY;
737
738 if (deadline) {
739 /* Convert duration parameter from stream timebase to microseconds */
740 uint64_t duration_us;
741
742 VPX_STATIC_ASSERT(TICKS_PER_SEC > 1000000 &&
743 (TICKS_PER_SEC % 1000000) == 0);
744
745 duration_us = duration * (uint64_t)ctx->timestamp_ratio.num /
746 (ctx->timestamp_ratio.den * (TICKS_PER_SEC / 1000000));
747
748 /* If the deadline is more that the duration this frame is to be shown,
749 * use good quality mode. Otherwise use realtime mode.
750 */
751 new_qc = (deadline > duration_us) ? MODE_GOODQUALITY : MODE_REALTIME;
752 }
753
754#else
755 (void)duration;
756 new_qc = MODE_REALTIME;
757#endif
758
759 if (deadline == VPX_DL_REALTIME) {
760 new_qc = MODE_REALTIME;
761 } else if (ctx->cfg.g_pass == VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS) {
762 new_qc = MODE_FIRSTPASS;
763 } else if (ctx->cfg.g_pass == VPX_RC_LAST_PASS) {
764 new_qc =
765 (new_qc == MODE_BESTQUALITY) ? MODE_SECONDPASS_BEST : MODE_SECONDPASS;
766 }
767
768 if (ctx->oxcf.Mode != new_qc) {
769 ctx->oxcf.Mode = new_qc;
770 vp8_change_config(ctx->cpi, &ctx->oxcf);
771 }
772}
773
774static vpx_codec_err_t set_reference_and_update(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
775 vpx_enc_frame_flags_t flags) {
776 /* Handle Flags */
777 if (((flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_GF) && (flags & VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_GF)) ||
778 ((flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_ARF) && (flags & VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_ARF))) {
779 ctx->base.err_detail = "Conflicting flags.";
780 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
781 }
782
783 if (flags &
784 (VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_LAST | VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_GF | VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_ARF)) {
785 int ref = 7;
786
787 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_LAST) ref ^= VP8_LAST_FRAME;
788
789 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_GF) ref ^= VP8_GOLD_FRAME;
790
791 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_REF_ARF) ref ^= VP8_ALTR_FRAME;
792
793 vp8_use_as_reference(ctx->cpi, ref);
794 }
795
796 if (flags &
797 (VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_LAST | VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_GF | VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_ARF |
798 VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_GF | VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_ARF)) {
799 int upd = 7;
800
801 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_LAST) upd ^= VP8_LAST_FRAME;
802
803 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_GF) upd ^= VP8_GOLD_FRAME;
804
805 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_ARF) upd ^= VP8_ALTR_FRAME;
806
807 vp8_update_reference(ctx->cpi, upd);
808 }
809
810 if (flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_ENTROPY) {
811 vp8_update_entropy(ctx->cpi, 0);
812 }
813
814 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
815}
816
817static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_encode(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
818 const vpx_image_t *img, vpx_codec_pts_t pts,
819 unsigned long duration,
820 vpx_enc_frame_flags_t enc_flags,
821 unsigned long deadline) {
822 volatile vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
823 // Make a copy as volatile to avoid -Wclobbered with longjmp.
824 volatile vpx_enc_frame_flags_t flags = enc_flags;
825 volatile vpx_codec_pts_t pts_val = pts;
826
827 if (!ctx->cfg.rc_target_bitrate) {
828#if CONFIG_MULTI_RES_ENCODING
829 if (!ctx->cpi) return VPX_CODEC_ERROR;
830 if (ctx->cpi->oxcf.mr_total_resolutions > 1) {
831 LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO *low_res_frame_info =
832 (LOWER_RES_FRAME_INFO *)ctx->cpi->oxcf.mr_low_res_mode_info;
833 if (!low_res_frame_info) return VPX_CODEC_ERROR;
834 low_res_frame_info->skip_encoding_prev_stream = 1;
835 if (ctx->cpi->oxcf.mr_encoder_id == 0)
836 low_res_frame_info->skip_encoding_base_stream = 1;
837 }
838#endif
839 return res;
840 }
841
842 if (img) res = validate_img(ctx, img);
843
844 if (!res) res = validate_config(ctx, &ctx->cfg, &ctx->vp8_cfg, 1);
845
846 if (!ctx->pts_offset_initialized) {
847 ctx->pts_offset = pts_val;
848 ctx->pts_offset_initialized = 1;
849 }
850 pts_val -= ctx->pts_offset;
851
852 pick_quickcompress_mode(ctx, duration, deadline);
853 vpx_codec_pkt_list_init(&ctx->pkt_list);
854
855 // If no flags are set in the encode call, then use the frame flags as
856 // defined via the control function: vp8e_set_frame_flags.
857 if (!flags) {
858 flags = ctx->control_frame_flags;
859 }
860 ctx->control_frame_flags = 0;
861
862 if (!res) res = set_reference_and_update(ctx, flags);
863
864 /* Handle fixed keyframe intervals */
865 if (ctx->cfg.kf_mode == VPX_KF_AUTO &&
866 ctx->cfg.kf_min_dist == ctx->cfg.kf_max_dist) {
867 if (++ctx->fixed_kf_cntr > ctx->cfg.kf_min_dist) {
868 flags |= VPX_EFLAG_FORCE_KF;
869 ctx->fixed_kf_cntr = 1;
870 }
871 }
872
873 if (setjmp(ctx->cpi->common.error.jmp)) {
874 ctx->cpi->common.error.setjmp = 0;
875 vpx_clear_system_state();
876 return VPX_CODEC_CORRUPT_FRAME;
877 }
878
879 /* Initialize the encoder instance on the first frame*/
880 if (!res && ctx->cpi) {
881 unsigned int lib_flags;
882 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG sd;
883 int64_t dst_time_stamp, dst_end_time_stamp;
884 size_t size, cx_data_sz;
885 unsigned char *cx_data;
886 unsigned char *cx_data_end;
887 int comp_data_state = 0;
888
889 /* Set up internal flags */
890 if (ctx->base.init_flags & VPX_CODEC_USE_PSNR) {
891 ((VP8_COMP *)ctx->cpi)->b_calculate_psnr = 1;
892 }
893
894 if (ctx->base.init_flags & VPX_CODEC_USE_OUTPUT_PARTITION) {
895 ((VP8_COMP *)ctx->cpi)->output_partition = 1;
896 }
897
898 /* Convert API flags to internal codec lib flags */
899 lib_flags = (flags & VPX_EFLAG_FORCE_KF) ? FRAMEFLAGS_KEY : 0;
900
901 dst_time_stamp =
902 pts_val * ctx->timestamp_ratio.num / ctx->timestamp_ratio.den;
903 dst_end_time_stamp = (pts_val + (int64_t)duration) *
904 ctx->timestamp_ratio.num / ctx->timestamp_ratio.den;
905
906 if (img != NULL) {
907 res = image2yuvconfig(img, &sd);
908
909 if (vp8_receive_raw_frame(ctx->cpi, ctx->next_frame_flag | lib_flags, &sd,
910 dst_time_stamp, dst_end_time_stamp)) {
911 VP8_COMP *cpi = (VP8_COMP *)ctx->cpi;
912 res = update_error_state(ctx, &cpi->common.error);
913 }
914
915 /* reset for next frame */
916 ctx->next_frame_flag = 0;
917 }
918
919 cx_data = ctx->cx_data;
920 cx_data_sz = ctx->cx_data_sz;
921 cx_data_end = ctx->cx_data + cx_data_sz;
922 lib_flags = 0;
923
924 ctx->cpi->common.error.setjmp = 1;
925
926 while (cx_data_sz >= ctx->cx_data_sz / 2) {
927 comp_data_state = vp8_get_compressed_data(
928 ctx->cpi, &lib_flags, &size, cx_data, cx_data_end, &dst_time_stamp,
929 &dst_end_time_stamp, !img);
930
931 if (comp_data_state == VPX_CODEC_CORRUPT_FRAME) {
932 return VPX_CODEC_CORRUPT_FRAME;
933 } else if (comp_data_state == -1) {
934 break;
935 }
936
937 if (size) {
938 vpx_codec_pts_t round, delta;
939 vpx_codec_cx_pkt_t pkt;
940 VP8_COMP *cpi = (VP8_COMP *)ctx->cpi;
941
942 /* Add the frame packet to the list of returned packets. */
943 round = (vpx_codec_pts_t)ctx->timestamp_ratio.num / 2;
944 if (round > 0) --round;
945 delta = (dst_end_time_stamp - dst_time_stamp);
946 pkt.kind = VPX_CODEC_CX_FRAME_PKT;
947 pkt.data.frame.pts =
948 (dst_time_stamp * ctx->timestamp_ratio.den + round) /
949 ctx->timestamp_ratio.num +
950 ctx->pts_offset;
951 pkt.data.frame.duration =
952 (unsigned long)((delta * ctx->timestamp_ratio.den + round) /
953 ctx->timestamp_ratio.num);
954 pkt.data.frame.flags = lib_flags << 16;
955 pkt.data.frame.width[0] = cpi->common.Width;
956 pkt.data.frame.height[0] = cpi->common.Height;
957 pkt.data.frame.spatial_layer_encoded[0] = 1;
958
959 if (lib_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY) {
960 pkt.data.frame.flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_KEY;
961 }
962
963 if (!cpi->common.show_frame) {
964 pkt.data.frame.flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_INVISIBLE;
965
966 /* This timestamp should be as close as possible to the
967 * prior PTS so that if a decoder uses pts to schedule when
968 * to do this, we start right after last frame was decoded.
969 * Invisible frames have no duration.
970 */
971 pkt.data.frame.pts =
972 ((cpi->last_time_stamp_seen * ctx->timestamp_ratio.den + round) /
973 ctx->timestamp_ratio.num) +
974 ctx->pts_offset + 1;
975 pkt.data.frame.duration = 0;
976 }
977
978 if (cpi->droppable) pkt.data.frame.flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_DROPPABLE;
979
980 if (cpi->output_partition) {
981 int i;
982 const int num_partitions =
983 (1 << cpi->common.multi_token_partition) + 1;
984
985 pkt.data.frame.flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_FRAGMENT;
986
987 for (i = 0; i < num_partitions; ++i) {
988#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY & CONFIG_ONTHEFLY_BITPACKING
989 pkt.data.frame.buf = cpi->partition_d[i];
990#else
991 pkt.data.frame.buf = cx_data;
992 cx_data += cpi->partition_sz[i];
993 cx_data_sz -= cpi->partition_sz[i];
994#endif
995 pkt.data.frame.sz = cpi->partition_sz[i];
996 pkt.data.frame.partition_id = i;
997 /* don't set the fragment bit for the last partition */
998 if (i == (num_partitions - 1)) {
999 pkt.data.frame.flags &= ~VPX_FRAME_IS_FRAGMENT;
1000 }
1001 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &pkt);
1002 }
1003#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY & CONFIG_ONTHEFLY_BITPACKING
1004 /* In lagged mode the encoder can buffer multiple frames.
1005 * We don't want this in partitioned output because
1006 * partitions are spread all over the output buffer.
1007 * So, force an exit!
1008 */
1009 cx_data_sz -= ctx->cx_data_sz / 2;
1010#endif
1011 } else {
1012 pkt.data.frame.buf = cx_data;
1013 pkt.data.frame.sz = size;
1014 pkt.data.frame.partition_id = -1;
1015 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &pkt);
1016 cx_data += size;
1017 cx_data_sz -= size;
1018 }
1019 }
1020 }
1021 }
1022
1023 return res;
1024}

1027 vpx_codec_iter_t *iter) {

1080
1081static vpx_image_t *vp8e_get_preview(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx) {
1082 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG sd;
1083 vp8_ppflags_t flags;
1084 vp8_zero(flags);
1085
1086 if (ctx->preview_ppcfg.post_proc_flag) {
1087 flags.post_proc_flag = ctx->preview_ppcfg.post_proc_flag;
1088 flags.deblocking_level = ctx->preview_ppcfg.deblocking_level;
1089 flags.noise_level = ctx->preview_ppcfg.noise_level;
1090 }
1091
1092 if (0 == vp8_get_preview_raw_frame(ctx->cpi, &sd, &flags)) {
1093 /*
1094 vpx_img_wrap(&ctx->preview_img, VPX_IMG_FMT_YV12,
1095 sd.y_width + 2*VP8BORDERINPIXELS,
1096 sd.y_height + 2*VP8BORDERINPIXELS,
1097 1,
1098 sd.buffer_alloc);
1099 vpx_img_set_rect(&ctx->preview_img,
1100 VP8BORDERINPIXELS, VP8BORDERINPIXELS,
1101 sd.y_width, sd.y_height);
1102 */
1103
1104 ctx->preview_img.bps = 12;
1105 ctx->preview_img.planes[VPX_PLANE_Y] = sd.y_buffer;
1106 ctx->preview_img.planes[VPX_PLANE_U] = sd.u_buffer;
1107 ctx->preview_img.planes[VPX_PLANE_V] = sd.v_buffer;
1108
1109 ctx->preview_img.fmt = VPX_IMG_FMT_I420;
1110 ctx->preview_img.x_chroma_shift = 1;
1111 ctx->preview_img.y_chroma_shift = 1;
1112
1113 ctx->preview_img.d_w = sd.y_width;
1114 ctx->preview_img.d_h = sd.y_height;
1115 ctx->preview_img.stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] = sd.y_stride;
1116 ctx->preview_img.stride[VPX_PLANE_U] = sd.uv_stride;
1117 ctx->preview_img.stride[VPX_PLANE_V] = sd.uv_stride;
1118 ctx->preview_img.w = sd.y_width;
1119 ctx->preview_img.h = sd.y_height;
1120
1121 return &ctx->preview_img;
1122 } else {
1123 return NULL;
1124 }
1125}

1179static vpx_codec_err_t vp8e_set_scalemode(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
1180 va_list args) {
1181 vpx_scaling_mode_t *data = va_arg(args, vpx_scaling_mode_t *);
1182
1183 if (data) {
1184 int res;
1185 vpx_scaling_mode_t scalemode = *(vpx_scaling_mode_t *)data;
1186 res = vp8_set_internal_size(ctx->cpi, (VPX_SCALING)scalemode.h_scaling_mode,
1187 (VPX_SCALING)scalemode.v_scaling_mode);
1188
1189 if (!res) {
1190 /*force next frame a key frame to effect scaling mode */
1191 ctx->next_frame_flag |= FRAMEFLAGS_KEY;
1192 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
1193 } else {
1194 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
1195 }
1196 } else {
1197 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
1198 }
